I. Surya, thou mountest up to meet the hero famous for his wealth, Who hurls the bolt and works for men;
p:Him who with might of both his arms broke nine-and-ninety castles down, Slew Vritra and smote Ahi dead.
p:This Indra is our gracious friend. He sends, like a full-streaming cow, Riches in horses, kine, and corn.
